<<View Mode>>

Generally, you do not want to see <<all>> messages
in the database. There may be too many, some you
may have already read, others may be old, etc.
For this reason, CrossPoint allows you to select
which messages to read.

The following selection criteria are available:


<<All>>    All messages are displayed.

<<Unread>> All messages that you have not read,
       regardless of age.

<<New>>    Shows messages since the last netcall or
       since importing a Puffer-File. Empty netcalls
       or Puffers are not counted.

<<Today>>  Selects messages that came in on the current
       date.

<<Date>>   Selects messages that came in after a date,
       which you may specify.

<<Time>>   You can fine tune the date above to specify a
       a time of day, to filter more precisely.

<<Save>>   Saves a set time as a dummy time of last
       netcall. Thus, you can save the time at which
       a netcall was made with this setting, make
       subsequent netcalls but still use "New" to
       call up all messages since the saved time.

When setting dates or times, the "+" & "-" keys can
be used to step through single days or minutes.

