158
The FIDO Mailer in CrossPoint supports both connect
protocols YooHoo and EMSI. XP will always try to use
EMSI, the better of the two, if the other side
supports it.

Normally you should leave the EMSI switch ON.
But if you should get problems with EMSI netcalls,
you can force CrossPoint to use YooHoo by switching
EMSI off. If problems occur, you can often find the
cause noted in the log file XP runs on FIDO
activities, XPFIDO.LOG. (Read it with an ordinary
editor)
@
159
Many Fido Boxes have a radio clock like DCF77 in
Germany, keeping them always synchronised to accurate
time. An EMSI netcall often sends the time, and by
setting this switch you can have your PC use this
time to set its internal clock, synchronising you
also to accurate time (within about +/- 2 sec.).

If you use the [programmed timing lists] for Cross-@11507
Point activities, you could even have it call a box
with a radio clock specially, at regular intervals,
just to get the time, even if you don't poll Fido
otherwise!
