8020
With this program, all messages going to the server
are [packed], or compressed. You select the settings@4006
for <<compress>>, <<freeze>>, or <<gzip>> by press-
ing F2. If you prefer to transfer [unpacked], you can@4006
leave this field empty.

Compress is supported by nearly all UUCP-servers,
Freeze by most; gzip (Gnu ZIP) is pretty new but
getting popular fast. If in doubt ask your systems
operator. If several packers are on offer, you can
mostly change without special agreement with the
server.

Compress offers extra possibilities, a choice between
12 bit (parameter -b12, less compression) and 16 bit,
(parameter -b16, higher compression), but again,
consult your system operator if in doubt.

Here some quick guidance:
(+ = good, o = medium, - = bad)

                ³     Speed       ³ Compression
ÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÅÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÅÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄ
compress 12-Bit ³       +         ³     -
compress 16-Bit ³       +         ³     o
freeze          ³       -         ³     +
gzip            ³       o         ³     +

@
