These commands will be sent to the modem <<BEFORE>> every
Netcall, regardless of which Server you are calling.
It is the default init string and will be sent before
the Server-specific init string as defined in
"/Edit/Servers/Edit/Modem". Consult your modem
handbook if you are not sure what commands should be
sent to initialise your modem.

The preset is:

    ATZ\\AT S0=0 Q0 E1 M1 V1 X4

    AT   = Attention (starts every command)
    Z    = Recall stored profile0
    S0=0 = switches Auto Answer-Mode off
    Q0   = Show result codes
    E1   = "Command echo" on
    M1   = Loudspeaker until connect
    V1   = Verbal result codes
    X4   = Recognise dial and busy tones

It is sensible to find the settings that suit your
situation best and store them in one of the modem
profiles (usually AT&Wx). It can include the above
and others, then you need only reset with: ATZx
instead of typing it all in.

Having this default setting and a Server-specific
setting allows flexibility.

If you wish to send a <CR> to the modem, you can
put a "\\" in the line. After this a new AT will be
necessary before carrying on. eg. ATE1\\ATS13=32.
This is usually not necessary as all the commands can
be strung together after one AT but occasionally, a
modem will need a <CR> after certain commands, before
it is accepted properly.

