<<[x]>>  Use ring signal line
<<[ ]>>  Ignore ring signal line

If an incoming call (ring signal) should occur while
CrossPoint is pausing between Netcalls, CrossPoint
will delay the Netcall for up to 5 minutes.

(Note, if CrossPoint tries to make a Netcall when
somebody is calling, it will effectively answer the
phone, which will probably cause difficulties all
round!)

If the ring signal line is not connected, as is the
case with some cheap modem cables, CrossPoint will
incorrectly report an incoming call, so this function
should be set to "ignore".

Tip: Get a decent modem cable :-)

