You can display the message header in the lister as
you wish:


<<Insert>>  inserts a line not presently displayed.
        (except dividing lines, which can occur any
        time.

<<Move>>    Moves the current line to another
        position. Move the cursor (after pressing M)
        to the position you want the line to appear,
        and press <Enter>.
        <Esc> aborts.

<<Delete>>   Does not display the selected line any
         more.

<<OK>>       Confirm changes and exit.


The lines Sender, Recipient, Subject, Date and Size
should not require further explanation.
This information is available in *all* messages if
you choose to display it. Other lines are displayed,
even if selected, only when the information is
actually in the header (the brackets indicate
information of this type)


<<Path:>>       Shows the route the message has taken
            in getting to you. All nets show this.

<<Message-ID:>> A "unique" message identification;
            sometimes really unique world wide, or
            maybe only fairly locally or for a
            limited time period.

<<Reference-ID:>>  The Message-ID of the message a
               reply is replying to.

<<Maus-PM-Status:>>  the current status of a PM in
                 MausNet; see XPOINT.DOC.


All other lines are only valid for ZConnect and
RFC-Nets (UseNet / "UUCP"):

<<Followup to:>> The newsgroup where public
             replies to a newsgroup message should be
             put.

<<Reply to:>> Address for PM-Replies

<<Copies to:>>   Addresses of other recipients, who
             should get a copy of the message (can
             also be a newsgroup).

<<File:>>        If it is a file to be sent, the
             name and date/time. Optional; a file can
             be received without a name or date/time.

<<Error:>>     Error message from a box program or a
           CrossPoint message converter.

<<Software:>>  The software with which the message
           was produced (or forwarded).

<<Status:>>     Various status information, eg.
            Confirm Receipt etc.

All other lines should be pretty self explanatory.
