<<Message / Extract / UUdecode

In some nets binary messages are transferred using
UUcode (Unix-to-Unix-Coding). They look like this:


begin 644 datei.ext
M1TE&.#=A\@ +@ 9       /___RP     @ +@ 0 "^XR/J<OM#Z.
M^P^&XDB6YHFFZLJV[\@O'\DS7]HWG^L[W_@\,"H?$HO&(3"J7S*
M]8K-:K?<KO<+#HO'Y++YC$ZKU^RV^PV/R^?TNOV.S^OW_+[_#Q\@

You can convert these messages back into their proper
form using the built in UUdecoder in CrossPoint. Any
extra text at the beginning or the end is ignored.
You can decode more than one marked message, to
reassemble a split file.

