11650
The following macros can be used in templates
(except signatures), and will be replaced at the time
of writing by the valid text.

  $DATUM     -  the current date
  $DATE      -  the current date in American format
  $UHRZEIT   -  the current time
  $TAG       -  the day of the week
  $TAG2      -  the short form for day of the week

The following macros may NOT be used in templates for
messages for <<newsgroups>>.


  $USER      -  The sender of the message being
                replied to, for PMs the current
                addressee.
  $MUSER     -  the same, but without \@BOX
  $BOX       -  the Box name for above
  $TUSER     -  again the same name, but in the usual
                FIDO or Maus net form, with capitals
                and small letters.
  $PSEUDO    -  The users Pseudonym. If you have
                entered something in the Comment box
                for a user (User/Special/Edit) in the
                form P:A_Name, then "A_Name" will be
                used (can be used for putting their
                real name in!). Otherwise it will be
                evaluated the same as $TUSER
  $VPSEUDO   -  the same as $PSEUDO, but $VORNAME
                (first name) will be used instead of
                $TUSER.
  $VORNAME   -  the first name of the user - works
                only in nets that use real names and
                not pseudos.
  $FIDOEMPF  -  the addressee in a FIDO area message.

The other macros are only permitted in Quote and
Forward templates.

  $BRETT     -  The name of the origin newsgroup
  $AREA      -  the name of the origin newsgroup for
                FIDO & MausNet messages
  $NEWSGROUP -  the name of the origin newsgroup in
                dot notation as usual in the usenet
  $BETREFF   -  The subject of the original message
  $ERSTELLT  -  The date of the original message
  $MSGDATE   -  the date American style
  $ERSTTAG   -  the weekday of the date of writing
  $ERSTTAG2  -  short form of the weekday
  $ERSTZEIT  -  The time of day of writing the
                original message
  $ERHALTEN  -  date of receipt
  $MSGID     -  the Message-ID of the original
                message

The following macros are only usable in Z-Netz and
Magic-compatible nets:

  $RNAME     -  The real name of the original sender
  $(RNAME)   -  as $RNAME, but in brackets

The real name is inserted followed by a space.
If no real name is available, these macros are empty.

