4004
<<Direct Mail>> is sent by your server box directly, by
calling the recipient server box directly, but not
necessarily immediately. It will probably be done
during the night at cheap telephone rates.

<<Express Mail>> is sent immediately. Your server box, as
soon as it receives the message from you, rings up
the recipient box as soon as possible to deposit the
message. This will probably be more expensive.

Beware! Both methods cost money, and depending on
your server, they may not be cheap. Usually a
fixed fee plus a charge per kilobyte.

