<< Nodelists & Nodediffs (FIDO)

Fido still uses the addressing system that all FIDO
systems (yes, world wide!) are to be found in a huge
list, which is updated weekly. This list is called
the <<Nodelist>>, and contains details of each FIDO node
(name, place, sysop, tel.no., modem etc. etc.).

If you wish to communicate directly with FIDO boxes
You must have this list available, because the FIDO
point program (in this case CrossPoint), must check
against the nodelist before it makes contact.

(There are also programs for browsing this list, to
glean information from it, search for boxes, sysops
or whatever.)

At the beginning you will need to get the complete
list once.

This list is very large, and to save everybody having
to get it every week, each week only the
*differences* to the last list are transported, in a
much smaller file called a <<NODEDIFF>>. As long as you
get this each week without fail, CrossPoint can
update your NodeList to the latest level. But if you
miss one, the chain is broken and you have to get a
complete new list.

You can have your FIDO node (server) send you the
nodediff each week. They are always packed with ARC.

If you check the box "import diffs automatically"
under the menu /Fido/Options, CrossPoint will
recognise when a nodediff comes, and unpack it (make
sure ARC is available; see /Config/External/unpacker)
and import it automatically.

Otherwise it lands in the subdirectory for received
files, you must <<unpack it>> and import it by hand under
/Fido/Nodelist/Read Diff

Which week the NodeList (and the nodediff) is for is
shown in its filename extension.

Press <Enter> to read about [Fido addresses].@4010

<<See also FIDO.DOC, "nodelists"

